09/15/80	lv_attached

Syntax:  lv_attached lv_name


Function:	 returns true if the volume specified (i.e., the lv_name
argument) is attached to the user's process or if the volume is a
public logical volume; otherwise it returns false.


Arguments:
lv_name
   is the name of the logical volume.


Syntax as active function:  [lv_attached lv_name]
